data.text:
According to this article The British public still have no idea what they voted for with Brexit – it’s not elitist to admit it, it is claimed:

A survey carried out in the run up to the 2015 general election revealed that 69 per cent of Britons confessed to having “no interest in politics” while a staggering 59 per cent couldn’t even name the then-prime minister, David Cameron.
